President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in Louisiana and ordered federal assistance due to the emergency conditions caused by Tropical Storm Barry. The Department of Homeland Security, specifically the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), will coordinate disaster relief efforts to alleviate the hardship and suffering of the local population. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. The federal funding for emergency protective measures will be at 75 percent. John E. Long has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA news desk.